# Naming Conventions

**📚 Complete Guide**: `docs/conventions/naming-conventions.md`

## Critical Rules (STRICTLY ENFORCED)

### Files — `kebab-case.type.ts`

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Entity | `*.ts` | `user.ts` |
| Value Object | `*.ts` | `email.ts`, `user-id.ts` |
| Repository interface | `*.repository.interface.ts` | `user.repository.interface.ts` |
| Repository impl | `*.repository.ts` | `in-memory-user.repository.ts` |
| Service | `*.service.ts` | `user-creator.service.ts` |
| Event | `*.event.ts` | `user-registered.event.ts` |
| DTO | `*.dto.ts` | `user.dto.ts` |
| Controller | `*.controller.ts` | `auth.controller.ts` |

### Classes — `PascalCase`

```typescript
UserCreator, InMemoryUserRepository, Email, UserId, UserRole
```

### Methods — `camelCase`

```typescript
run(), findById(), getValue(), withPasswordHash()
```

### Packages — `@OneJs/package-name`

```typescript
import { Injectable } from '@OneJs/core'
import { EventBus } from '@OneJs/event-bus'
```

### Local packages — `@[scope]/package-name`

Define the scope in your workspace (e.g., `@dfs/`, `@myapp/`) in `package.json`.

## Layer Directory Structure

```
packages/<context>/
├── domain/
│   ├── entities/           # EntityBase<TId> subclasses
│   ├── value-objects/      # ValueObjectBase<T> subclasses
│   ├── repositories/       # Interface (port) definitions
│   ├── events/             # Domain event classes
│   └── services/           # Domain service classes
├── application/
│   ├── *.service.ts        # Use case services (run() entry point)
│   └── dtos/               # DTO classes for persistence boundaries
└── infrastructure/
    ├── repositories/       # Concrete adapters (InMemory, Prisma)
    └── controllers/        # HTTP/RPC controllers
```

## Services Must Have `run()`

```typescript
✅ Correct
class UserCreator { async run(email: Email, hash: PasswordHash): Promise<User> {} }

❌ Wrong
class UserCreator { async create(email: string): Promise<User> {} }
```
